Built to the exacting standards demanded by the aeropsace industry, each Beadlight reading light is made by hand and wrapped in English leather with hand stitching.

Featured Designer
Florence Knoll
In 1941 Florence Schust moved to New York after graduating from Cranbrook and working with many of the greatest architects in the world. There she met Hans Knoll, who was establishing a new furniture company. With Florence’s design skills and Hans’ business acumen and salesmanship, the pair, who married in 1946, grew the nascent company into an international arbiter of style and design. ABOUT US
The Past Perfect Collection offers an unrivalled choice of antique colonial furniture spanning the British, Dutch and Portuguese era in India. Imagine the romance of colonial European style courting Indian craftsmanship!
All furniture is carefully selected and lovingly restored to its former glory. These pieces can add that special character to your home, silently speaking to you of a bygone era. Own a treasure of the past and make the present just perfect!

Shop the new shipment at The Past Perfect Collection. Featuring our latest acquisitions of antique furniture. The perfect partnership of history and quality, they were made during colonial times in India and are greatly admired on both sides of the cultural divide. Each piece is a genuine antique which has been lovingly restored.
Discover more about our Antique Furniture.

Singapore’s finest antique store specialises in antique colonial furniture dating back to the British, Dutch and Portuguese era in India. It was established in 2007 by the owners Pieter and Marie-Hélène van Houten, who are passionate antique collectors. They personally select the pieces and have them restored to their former glory in India before they are shipped to Singapore.
